### Test Authorization Flow - CAP BDC Application

### 1. Get all ARMaster records (Master Authorization Table)
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ARMaster
Accept: application/json

### 2. Get all ApproverMaster records (Master Authorization Table)
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ApproverMaster
Accept: application/json

### 3. Create AR Request - Valid ServiceName (Should succeed and copy AccessKey)
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ARChangeLog
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SERVICE_NAME": "FinanceService",
  "REQUESTOR": "john.doe@company.com",
  "SHORT_DESCRIPTION__C": "Request access to Finance Service",
  "ROLE_NAME": "Finance_User",
  "ENTITY_NAME": "Finance_Entity",
  "COMPANY_CODE": "1000",
  "COUNTRY_LOCATION": "USA",
  "BUSINESS_UNIT": "Corporate Finance",
  "TRIGRAM_COMPANY": "FIN",
  "ORGANIZATION_UNIT": "Finance Dept",
  "VALID_FROM": "2024-01-20",
  "VALID_TO": "2024-12-31"
}

### 4. Create AR Request - Invalid ServiceName (Should fail with error)
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ARChangeLog
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SERVICE_NAME": "InvalidService",
  "REQUESTOR": "jane.smith@company.com",
  "SHORT_DESCRIPTION__C": "Request access to Invalid Service"
}

### 5. Create AR Request - Missing ServiceName (Should fail with error)
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ARChangeLog
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "REQUESTOR": "test.user@company.com",
  "SHORT_DESCRIPTION__C": "Request without service name"
}

### 6. Create Approver Request - Valid ServiceName (Should succeed and copy AccessKey)
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ApproverChangeLog
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SERVICE_NAME": "HRService",
  "REQUESTOR": "approver1@company.com",
  "SHORT_DESCRIPTION__C": "Request HR approver access",
  "ROLE_NAME": "HR_Approver_L1",
  "ENTITY_NAME": "HR_Entity",
  "COMPANY_CODE": "2000",
  "COUNTRY_LOCATION": "Germany",
  "BUSINESS_UNIT": "Human Resources",
  "TRIGRAM_COMPANY": "HRD",
  "APPROVER": "hr.manager@company.com",
  "VALID_FROM": "2024-01-20",
  "VALID_TO": "2024-12-31"
}

### 7. Create Approver Request - Invalid ServiceName (Should fail with error)
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ApproverChangeLog
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SERVICE_NAME": "NonExistentService",
  "REQUESTOR": "approver2@company.com",
  "SHORT_DESCRIPTION__C": "Request invalid service access"
}

### 8. Get all AR Requests (Check ACCESS_KEY is populated)
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ARChangeLog
Accept: application/json

### 9. Get all Approver Requests (Check ACCESS_KEY is populated)
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ApproverChangeLog
Accept: application/json

### 10. Create AR Request - ProcurementService
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ARChangeLog
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SERVICE_NAME": "ProcurementService",
  "REQUESTOR": "procurement.user@company.com",
  "SHORT_DESCRIPTION__C": "Need procurement access",
  "ROLE_NAME": "Procurement_Buyer",
  "ENTITY_NAME": "Procurement_Entity",
  "COMPANY_CODE": "3000",
  "COUNTRY_LOCATION": "UK",
  "BUSINESS_UNIT": "Operations",
  "PURCHASE_ORGANIZATION": "PO_EMEA",
  "REGION_SITE": "London",
  "VALID_FROM": "2024-02-01",
  "VALID_TO": "2024-12-31"
}

### 11. Create AR Request - SalesService
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/bdc/ARChangeLog
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Basic admin:admin

{
  "SERVICE_NAME": "SalesService",
  "REQUESTOR": "sales.rep@company.com",
  "SHORT_DESCRIPTION__C": "Sales access request",
  "ROLE_NAME": "Sales_Representative",
  "ENTITY_NAME": "Sales_Entity",
  "COMPANY_CODE": "4000",
  "COUNTRY_LOCATION": "France",
  "BUSINESS_UNIT": "Sales",
  "SALES_ORGANIZATION": "SO_EMEA",
  "MARKET_AREA": "Western Europe",
  "REGION_SITE": "Paris",
  "VALID_FROM": "2024-02-01",
  "VALID_TO": "2024-12-31",
  "IsActiveEntity": true 
}

